liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The association representing Qantas Group pilots hopes the leadership change at Qantas will provide a 'circuit breaker'. The Australian and International Pilots Association President Captain Tony Lucas says the association looks forward to working with incoming CEO Vanessa Hudson. "There is much work to be done, however we trust that Ms Hudson recognises the power of respecting and valuing all Qantas staff and how that can play a significant role in the renewal of the airline. The Spirit of Australia may be deflated, but it is not defeated and if we all work together, I'm confident Qantas can be great once more."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: What the pilots have to say about Qantas

children.content: The association representing Qantas Group pilots hopes the leadership change at Qantas will provide a 'circuit breaker'.

The Spirit of Australia may be deflated, but it is not defeated and if we all work together, I'm confident Qantas can be great once more."

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The ASX 200 has opened lower, with US markets closed for Labor Day. The benchmark index dropped -0.5% to 7,283 points at 10:15am AEST. The broader All Ordinaries index also fell -0.5%, to 7486 points. Qantas shares dropped -0.5% on the opening bell, after CEO Alan Joyce announced he will step down from the top job two months early. Vanessa Hudgen will take over as of tomorrow. Meanwhile, the Reserve Bank will meet today to decide the official cash rate. It's expected to stay on hold at 4.1%. liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Australian Alex de Minaur has been dumped out of the US Open in the fourth round by Daniil Medvedev, with the former world number one charging to a 2-6, 6-4, 6-1, 6-2 win. After looking in total control in the first set, de Minaur was overrun by the class of Russia's Medvedev, who hit his stride and played some of his best tennis of the tournament to finish off the 13th seed, who was Australia's last representative in either singles draw. Medvedev is now into an all-Russian quarterfinal against eighth seed Andrey Rublev.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Alex de Minaur knocked out of US Open

featuredLink.title: No more Australians in the US Open singles as Alex de Minaur dumped out by former champion
